# ── Build context hygiene ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Keeps the image small and, critically, prevents the host's node_modules
# (Windows binaries) from clobbering the Linux node_modules installed
# inside the frontend build stage.

# Node
**/node_modules
frontend/dist

# Python
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
backend/staticfiles
backend/media
backend/logs
**/.venv
**/venv

# Git / editor / CI
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
Jenkinsfile
tests

# Local junk
aa
aaaa
desktop.ini
**/desktop.ini
*.md

# NOTE: .env files are intentionally NOT ignored — Jenkins materialises
# backend/.env and frontend/.env into the workspace before the build so
# they can be baked in / read at runtime.
